purpose: The commit addresses a bug where queuing commands could lead to a use-after-free (UAF) issue when the HCI_UNREGISTER flag is set. It modifies hci_cmd_sync_queue to return an error in such cases, preventing the UAF.
The commit removes an unnecessary include of asm/termios.h in n_hdlc.c. It's part of cleaning up dependencies since another header already includes the necessary termios.h.
The commit updates the documentation for the 'store metric N/A' in the perf c2c tool. It reflects changes in the report table but does not alter functionality.
The commit addresses issues in vma lock handling during split operations, fixing race conditions and ensuring proper lock allocation. It modifies how VM_MAYSHARE is handled to prevent future issues.

The commit adds documentation for AVDD and MICVDD supplies in the dt-bindings for rt5682s codec. These supplies are already used elsewhere, so this is about updating the bindings to reflect their usage.

The commit addresses a resource leak in the zorro7xx SCSI driver by adding an iounmap() call in the remove function. This fixes an issue where resources were not properly freed, potentially leading to system instability.
The commit removes an unused 'work' field from struct mlx5e_async_ctx in the net/mlx5e component. This is a cleanup task to improve code quality by eliminating unnecessary elements.

This commit changes the data type of 'key_idx' in the cfg80211_auth_request struct from unsigned to signed. This adjustment is made to prevent static checker warnings when key is NULL, as -1 would be assigned in such cases. The change ensures that the code handles this scenario correctly without triggering warnings.
The commit sorts the CONFIG_SURFACE_PLATFORMS in defconfigs to match the order used by savedefconfig, ensuring consistency without functional changes.

The commit introduces a new function mcp251xfd_is_fd_mode() to replace an open-coded check for CAN-FD mode configuration in chip FIFOs. This improves code readability and maintainability by encapsulating the logic.
The commit modifies self-tests for RTC to skip execution when RTC is not present, preventing unnecessary test failures.
The commit removes a redundant assignment to the variable 'bytes' which was causing a dead store warning. This improves code clarity and fixes a static analysis warning.
The commit modifies the kernel to allow rcuscale without RCU Tasks, reducing kernel size and complexity by decoupling their presence.
The commit removes duplicated text in the spte.h file to improve code clarity.
The commit reverts a change that was causing issues with clock table population based on dcfclk. It addresses a failure where the system would not read properly when dcfclk states were disabled.
The commit adds a compatible string for the Renesas RZ/V2L SoC with Mali-G31 GPU in device tree bindings. It improves documentation but doesn't change functionality.

The commit renames the struct pcie_port to dw_pcie_rp for consistency with other naming conventions in the DW PCIe core driver. This involves a structural change to improve code readability and maintainability.

The commit fixes a Clang -Wformat warning by correcting the format specifier in a debug statement. The change ensures that the promoted integer type matches the format specifier, aligning with C11 standards and improving code correctness.
The commit fixes a bug in the MIPS compatibility branch range check by casting the upper bound to long for signed comparison, preventing issues with negative offsets.
The commit removes the HW_VAR_H2C_FW_P2P_PS_OFFLOAD case from SetHwReg8188EU() by directly calling a function, part of eliminating an unwanted HAL layer.
The commit addresses a sparse warning by declaring a non-global symbol as static, improving code quality.
The commit corrects an error in device tree bindings by removing incorrect interrupt flags for MDSS nodes, as they are not applicable since the provider is a single cell.
The commit modifies the struct ctrl_ref by allocating arrays to prepare for allowing drivers to change array sizes.
The commit adds support for additional PMICs and SoCs (SM8350, SC8280XP, SA8540P, SM8450) to the socinfo driver, expanding hardware compatibility.

The commit updates the rtl8xxxu Wi-Fi driver to recognize all possible chip versions (A-P) instead of displaying 'unknown' for versions beyond E. This involves modifying how chip cuts are handled in the driver.
The commit removes redundant .is_enabled state from PRCMU clocks as the core already manages enable counts, improving code quality.
The commit aims to reduce the use of #ifdef CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL by reorganizing code. It involves moving pt_ops macro and grouping function declarations, improving code structure.
The commit enables QUP and GPI DMA in the device tree for SM6350-Lena, preparing for future I2C node additions.
The commit involves correcting comments in the thermal driver for rzg2l. It replaces misleading terminology, fixes a typo, and adjusts comment formatting to adhere to coding standards.
The commit addresses an infinite loop issue in release_swfw_sync when failing to acquire the HW semaphore, particularly during hardware surprise removal. It adds error logging and exits gracefully.

The commit updates the pcm3168a driver to use modern ASoC DAI terminology for clocking, replacing old defines. This is a refactoring effort to align with current coding standards and improve code clarity.
The commit removes a redundant check for IS_SWAPFILE in NFS code. The condition was unnecessary as IS_SWAPFILE is always defined.
The commit implements GTP echo response handling to comply with the specification by sending ECHO_RSP messages containing necessary information elements.

The commit replaces cpumask_next_* functions with cpumask_first_* where appropriate, as the latter is more effective when starting from 0. It also creates a new cpumask_first_zero() function since it doesn't exist.

The commit removes a specific IOVAR call ('dtim_assoc') in the brcmfmac driver, which was causing a failure during roaming. This change stops the host driver from attempting to retrieve TIM information from firmware that is no longer supported.
This commit adds support for a platform without an amplifier by introducing a new board configuration (adl_rt5682) and connecting the alc5682 codec to SSP0, following Intel's BT offload design.
The commit modifies the kernel to fail zero-copy sendmsg operations when the socket doesn't support them, ensuring correct behavior by handling unsupported cases.
The commit modifies the loading of xeCJK.sty by adding a test for its existence before attempting to load it. This prevents errors on systems where the package might not be installed correctly.
The commit modifies the checkpatch script to ignore certain macro usages that were previously flagged as errors, allowing 'case' macros without parentheses.
The commit replaces simple-KMS helpers with atomic helpers to improve code structure and allow easier sharing among drivers without functional changes.
The commit adds a JPEG decode worker interface to enable three HWs running in parallel on MT8195, enhancing decoding efficiency.
The commit removes unnecessary VPRINTK() calls and the ata_scsi_dump_cdb() function, as their information is redundant with existing tracepoints. This improves code cleanliness and maintainability.

The commit adds support for zstate during extended vblank in the display driver. It modifies how vtotal and vblank are handled when entering and exiting freesync states, optimizing certain values to improve performance.

The commit fixes a CFI failure by correcting the type of the reset_type parameter in hqd_destroy(). This adjustment ensures that the function pointer's prototype matches the actual implementation, preventing the CFI violation.
The commit corrects the property name 'reset' to 'resets' in device tree bindings for STM32 pinctrl. It also adds 'additionalProperties: false' to prevent future validation issues.

This commit addresses a GCC 12 warning about array bounds in the ath9k driver. The change likely involves modifying code or adding a compiler flag to suppress the warning without altering the driver's functionality.
The commit replaces pm_runtime_get_sync with pm_runtime_resume_and_get in the crypto subsystem for sun8i-ss, aiming to simplify code.

The commit reorganizes the io_uring subsystem by moving fixed file installation and removal functions into the filetable code. It also modifies helper functions to use a context (ctx) instead of an io_kiocb, improving code structure.
The commit updates the device tree bindings to split G1 and G2 decoder nodes, allowing independent management through the vpu-blk-ctrl power domain controller.

The commit removes the IWL_DEVICE_BZ_COMMON macro from the iwlwifi configuration. This macro was only used once within another macro (IWL_DEVICE_BZ), so its contents are now directly included there, simplifying the code.
